Bird's Opening [The following game is, we believe, the longest game on record
as regards the number of moves, and it is also remarkable in other respects.
It was played in the fifth round of the handicap of the City of London Chess
Club between Messrs. Bird and Potter. Its issue was of great importance, as
the loser of this game was to be thrown out altogether while the winner
secured, at least, the second prize, the two players having previously won a
game each and made three draws. The game lasted sixteen hours, and was played
in three sittings.] CPQC iv (Apr. 1875) pp.240-3 notes by Wisker, not input} 1.
