421,871,603,1242,638,618,585,773,444,1096,957,2105,781,29990,29991,29996,29997,
29997,29998,29998,29999,29999] A02: Bird's Opening '***INTERCEPTION*** THRILL
ON THE EDGE OF THE CHESSBOARD In a dispute, now and again emerging at chess
websites or social media networks, on whether folks played chess better in the
past or in the present, the majority of respondents are quite confident with
the alleged supremacy against their forefathers. As far as I am concerned, I
am not so sure though. I could leave alone the numerous proponents of engine
based analysis of any chess game if I were sadly ignorant of the impact it
leaves on both their own and their reader's ability to think independently. As
to the second argument, an important consideration is comparison of beauty
between the moves of the past and the present. In an endless flow of modern
games, both standard and rapid, I am yet to discover the likes of Bird -
Morphy or Levitsky - Marshall with their stunning strikes out of the blue.
Karpov,Anatoly: 'Sulskis,Sar~unas: '***INTERCEPTION*** THRILL ON THE EDGE OF
THE CHESSBOARD In a dispute, now and again emerging at chess websites or
social media networks, on whether folks played chess better in the past or in
the present, the majority of respondents are quite confident with the alleged
supremacy against their forefathers. As far as I am concerned, I am not so
sure though. I could leave alone the numerous proponents of engine based
analysis of any chess game if I were sadly ignorant of the impact it leaves on
both their own and their reader's ability to think independently. As to the
second argument, an important consideration is comparison of beauty between
the moves of the past and the present. In an endless flow of modern games,
both standard and rapid, I am yet to discover the likes of Bird - Morphy or
Levitsky - Marshall with their stunning strikes out of the blue.''' Schallopp,
