-957,-945,-1217,-1214,-1198,-312,-1565,-1170] A03: Bird's Opening with 1...d5
Just to be perfectly clear, there is nothing to be learned here. If you wish
to click the Continue button then you will not really be missing anything. For
those who are up for a little entertainment, read on. There may be a time when
you are standing in line at the DMV, or waiting behind someone with a problem
at the pharmacy counter. That could be a good opportunity to put this section
to use. I was going to tell the story of the best game I did not win here, but
after a couple thousand words I decided below, but as I mentioned, there is
nothing to be learned here, so it is only there for those who may be curious.
Sometimes, something more than simply learning a specific move can be
instructive. Sometimes psychology actually can become a weapon. And sometimes
Bird's Opening has a major role to play, so it all somewhat ties together. So
when you've got a few moments with nothing to do then copy the below link,
paste it into your browser's address bar, and enjoy a story that always gives
me a bit of a smile when I think of it. [ https://birdsopeningforclubplayers.
wordpress.com/2023/08/05/the-best-game-i-did-not-win/ ] If you are curious
about the game then you can follow it below, though as I mentioned previously,
there really is nothing to learn here.} 1. f4 e6 2. e3 c5 3. Nf3 a6 4. b3 Nc6
